Before submitting any template, verify:

- [ ] Unique, memorable design (not generic AI slop)
- [ ] Distinctive typography (not Inter/Roboto/Arial)
- [ ] Cohesive color palette (not purple gradients)
- [ ] Responsive on mobile, tablet, desktop
- [ ] WCAG AA accessibility compliance
- [ ] Lighthouse score 90+
- [ ] All paths are relative (no absolute URLs)
- [ ] Works on Cloudflare, Vercel, Netlify
- [ ] Complete README.md
- [ ] Complete template.json
- [ ] MIT License included
- [ ] No console errors
- [ ] Cross-browser tested
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works
- [ ] Loading states implemented
- [ ] Error handling present
- [ ] Code is well-commented
- [ ] Dependencies are up to date
- [ ] .env.example provided if needed

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

- Using the same fonts across multiple templates
- Defaulting to centered layouts
- Forgetting mobile optimization
- Hardcoding absolute URLs
- Missing accessibility features
- Poor performance (slow loading)
- Incomplete documentation
- Missing error handling
- Breaking on subdirectory deployments
- Not testing on multiple hosts
- Committing sensitive data
- Using outdated dependencies

